data.text:
Martell Webster - Points

Martell Webster scores a career high 34 points (2013)

On March 16, 2013, Martell Webster set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 34 points in Washington's home win against Phoenix, 127-105. He also had 2 rebounds, 5 assists. He shot 3/8 from two, 7/10 from three, shooting at 55.6% from the field. He also shot 7/7 from the free-throw line.

Martell Webster - Rebounds

Martell Webster grabs a career high 13 rebounds (2009)

On November 21, 2009, Martell Webster set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 13 rebounds in Portland's home win against Minnesota, 106-78. He also had 21 points, 2 assists.

Martell Webster - Assists

Martell Webster gives a career high 7 assists (2013)

On November 27, 2013, Martell Webster set his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 7 assists in Washington's road win against Milwaukee, 92-100. He also had 18 points, 5 rebounds.

Martell Webster - Steals

Martell Webster has a career high 4 steals (2006)

On April 17, 2006, Martell Webster tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 4 steals in Portland's road loss against Golden State, 93-79. He also had 11 points, 4 rebounds and 3 assists.

Martell Webster - Blocks

Martell Webster blocks a career high 4 shots (2007)

On November 19, 2007, Martell Webster set his career high in blocks in a NBA game. That day he went for 4 blocks in Portland's road loss against Charlotte, 101-92. He also had 15 points, 6 rebounds.

Martell Webster - Efficiency

Martell Webster records a career high 35 efficiency rating (2013)

On December 16, 2013, Martell Webster set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 35 efficiency in Washington's road win against New York, 101-102. He also had 30 points, 5 rebounds and 3 assists.
